item.description:
Sometimes you I&rsquo;m need to create new FS on partition, which was already used for something else (another FS, RAID, LVM). I was wondering about most usable ways to clear metadata. Here is some I liked the most.
first {% highlight bash %} wipefs -a ${DEVICE} {% endhighlight %}
second {% highlight bash %} dd if=/dev/zero of=${DEVICE} bs=512 seek=$(( $(blockdev &ndash;getsz ${DEVICE}) - 1024 )) count=1024 {% endhighlight %}
third {% highlight bash %} dmraid -r -E ${DEVICE} {% endhighlight %}
